## Fixture authoring

Add a new fixture file under `/Users/jacegalloway/Documents/codebases/REMIBackend/src/services/scheduling/__fixtures__/linter-cases/` (the canonical directory â€” the TECH symlink picks it up automatically). See the `README.md` in that directory for the JSON shape. Re-run both test suites; both should pick up the new file with no test-source changes.

## What this rule does NOT cover

- The HTTP endpoints that consume the linter â€” those live in REMIBackend's reorganization routes.
- The review-screen UI that renders linter output â€” see `app/pending-reality/review.tsx` and the `usePendingRealityStore` selectors.
- The richer per-intent `LinterDependencyEdge` shape â€” that's the persisted form on `reorganization_intents.linter_dependency_edges`. The linter's flat `LinterIssue` output is the surface the review UI renders; the BE commit handler is responsible for mapping issues into per-intent edges before persisting.
- The Zod-4 backend upgrade that would let us collapse the duplication â€” separate tech-debt effort, currently unscheduled.
